All Classes

Class
Description
Counter
The table that the player can place one dish on
Disaster
A disaster in the game that the player has to account for and fix in a set amount of time.
DrawingSurface
the drawing surface for the game, and uses the ScreenSwitcher
FirstScreen
the opening screen for the player that shows the controls for the game and a button to start
Hole
The hole in the ground that the player drops food through
Ingredients
Ingredients can be picked up and have their own icons on the grid, extends the interactions class The ingredients are: onion, squirrel, rotten tomato, rabbit, smelly cheese, radioactive slime
Interactions
A superclass for anything that can be interacted with (picked up and dropped/used)
Main
main class to run the program and open up a new drawing surface also used to run music
Music
allows the game to play background music
Orders
The order class will be used to create an order, randomizing between the possible ingredients
Player
runs the player for the game, allows the player to move around the screen, pick up, and drop off objects
Screen
screens the player can use
ScreenSwitcher
interface for the screens
SecondScreen
 
ThirdScreen
The ending screen for the player that can take the player back to the menu screen
